The Proposal: -

Amravati district. Pahur Ta. Nandgaon Khandeshwar (Scheme Code-20054968) The original budget of the tap water supply scheme was prepared by the CEO, Zilla Parishad, Amravati vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2. The scheme has a discovered cost of Rs 62.86. Also, Reference No. 1 under Rs. 54,55,381 - Such a modest price has been granted administrative approval. Reference No. 5 of the Department. HARK has approved the bid for the scheme's surcharge under the letter dated 08.03.2023. Also, the Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Amravati proposed to give revised administrative approval to the proposed tap water supply scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here.

The letter dated 15.10.2024 has been submitted to the government. Reference No. 2 here. Under the letter dated 31.05.2024, the government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price as per the revised technical approval given by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Amravati.
The government's decision:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Dr. Pahur Ta. The Nandgaon SAL Tap Water Supply Scheme has been awarded a contract for an amount of Rs. 59,78,912 - (Rupees Sixty-nine lakhs seventy-eight thousand nine hundred and twelve only) is being revised with the approval of the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Supra 2024 / Q. 584 / UT W3 (E Office No-1909503)
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval as well as the original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for the implementation of the scheme, maintenance, repairs (subject to special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or renovation of machinery to meet the recurring expenditure incurred every year.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) A CAG report in 2013 shows that 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity bills. In fact, the Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned will be responsible for increasing the water tariff as per requirement so that the scheme remains financially viable.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.

2. Schemes for which tenders have been floated. The increased cost of revised cost of the scheme for which 21.06.2022 Yat has been sanctioned should be met from the sanctioned grant of Jal Jeevan Mission programme only.

The expenditure up to the limit should be met from the approved Central and State share grants as per the guidelines issued from time to time of the Jal Jeevan Mission programme. Further, as per the revised administrative approval, the remaining cost from the sanctioned cost to the discovered / approved cost should be met from the sanctioned grant of Jal Jeevan Mission programme only.
3. The revised administrative approval is the technicalities of the proposal received from the Regional Offices.

Government approval should not be taken into account in case of tender proceedings and territorial decisions or irregularities. Therefore, if such a case arises, the relevant enforcement mechanism will be solely responsible for it.

4. Revised administrative approval to the proposed scheme is provided by the Department of Finance. The Government Decision No. 1 of 2012 / Q. No. 30/2013 Regulations, Part II, Part I, Sub-section III, No.
(6) Paragraph No. is being granted as per the authority conferred on the department under 27 (a).
5. Shifting of connection is not permitted under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme" and should not be implemented if this provision is made in the revised scheme.
